Today, Golden has seen a small rebirth as new residents have moved into the area, building new homes and restoring others, but still it remains a sleepy village with vivid reminders of its more robust past. It is home to the Henderson Store, which sells Native American jewelry and pottery.<ref>{{cite web|title=Henderson Store|work=hendersonstore.com |url=http://www.hendersonstore.com/|accessdate=5 February 2012}}</ref>

